Osimhen will reportedly  undergo medical examination today  and could return to action with a protective mask next week. The Nigeria international suffered a cheekbone injury in a clash of heads with Inter defender Milan Skriniar at the end of November. He was ruled out of action for 90 days after undergoing surgery. The striker hoped to play in the Africa Cup of Nations with Nigeria thanks to a protective mask but was tested positive for COVID before the beginning of the tournament, so he was not included in the team.   Musa hints about AFCON farewell     Troubled Jamilu finally joins Eagles      Senegal, Morocco in good start   Osimhen has returned to Italy after recovering from COVID and will assess his injury today in a specialist visit with Gianpaolo Tartaro, the same doctor who performed the surgery almost two months ago. - Advertisement - In case of positive results, Osimhen could return to action in Napoli’s next Serie A game against Bologna, or against Salernitana on January 23. In any case, Osimhen would need to wear a protective mask to play competitive games over the next few weeks.